#Text=Tacoma
#Text=Tacoma in the state of Washington , is the state 's second-largest city , with just under 200,000 residents .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Tacoma often gets a negative description reminiscent of the one given to Oakland , California .
#Text=These negative vibes are equally unrealistic and often come from those who have never lived in or even visited the city .

#Text=While it has neither the tourist amenities of its neighbor Seattle to the north nor the suburban safety of Olympia to the south , you can certainly spend a few pleasant days in Tacoma and see the city 's dynamic art scene and its great ballet .
#Text=By plane
#Text=The ( SEA ) is the nearest airport for commercial flights .
#Text=It is 25 mi/40km north of Tacoma .
#Text=Sea-Tac airport serves much of the greater Seattle Metropolitan area and the Pacific NW .
#Text=Options besides taxi/limo or rental car are :
#Text=Sound Transit Rt #574 .
#Text=Daily express bus between Lakewood , Tacoma , Federal Way , Kent , SeaTac light rail station and the airport .
#Text=ShuttleExpress , ☏ +1425 981-7000 .
#Text=Operates shared and private shuttle services between the airport and hotels & residents within the Tacoma-Seattle- Bellevue - Everett corridor and its vicinity .
#Text=Catch them at the 3rd level of the parking garage .
#Text=During the morning commute hours ( 7-10AM ) , it may not be best to take this transportation if you go to downtown
#Text=Seattle unless you have a lot of baggage to take care of ; the more spacious Link Light Rail trains will get you there for about the same duration or even quicker .
#Text=Walk-ins are allowed for trips from the airport ( shared vans only ) , reservations necessary for trips to the airport .
#Text=Downtown from $ 18 .
#Text=Capital Aeroporter , toll-free : +1-800-962-3579 .
#Text=For areas mainly south of the airport ( Tacoma , Olympia , Auburn , Kent , Chehalis , Centralia , Shelton ) .
#Text=Bremerton-Kitsap Aeroporter , ( scheduled stop ) Dennys Restaurant @ 5924 6th Ave ( 6th & Pearl ) , ☏ +1360 876-1737 .
#Text=Connects the airport to Tacooma , Gig Harbor and the Kitsap Peninsula .
#Text=They go south on I-5 to Tacoma and over the Narrows Bridge along WA Hwy 16 to get to the Kitsap Peninsula rather than going across on the ferry from Seattle .
#Text=They also have a separate run between the airport and the Lewis-McChord Joint Military Base .
#Text=Be sure to have a valid DoD ID card to enter Lewis-McChord .
#Text=By car
#Text=Tacoma is along Interstate 5 ( I-5 ) , approximately 35 mi south of Seattle ( 35 min ) , 293 mi ( 5 hr ) southwest of Spokane , and 143 mi ( 2.5 hr ) north of Portland .
#Text=From Interstate 5 ( I-5 ) Tacoma is accessed from exits #136 ( " Port of Tacoma " ) through #127 ( " S Tacoma Way/WA-512 to Puyallup " ) along I-5 .

#Text=To get to downtown , exit off at the Interstate 705 off ramp at Exit 133 , just beyond the Tacoma dome if going south from I-5 , or continue along I-705 past downtown to Schuster Pkwy to get to old town , north Tacoma and the Ruston Way waterfront .
#Text=Continue to the next exit along I-5 to 132B to get to WA-16 going west towards Gig Harbor , Bremerton and for additional access to other parts of town .

#Text=To get to Joint Base Lewis McChord continue south past WA-512 to exits #125 ( " Bridgeport Way/McChord Field " ) , #123 ( " Thorne Ln " ) , 122 ( " Berkely Ave nearest access to Madigan Hospital and Camp Murray " ) , 120 ( " Joint Base Lewis-McChord " ) which is the location of the main gate & visitors center into the base , or 119 ( Dupont-Steilacoom Rd ) .
#Text=Access to the military base is controlled and a valid Dept. of Defense ( DoD ) ID and vehicle decal are required to be allowed through .
#Text=Otherwise see the visitors center off of exit 120 .
#Text=Exits 119-125 will come first before getting into Tacoma if going north on I-5 from Olympia .
#Text=From Interstate 90 ( I-90 ) coming from eastern Washington exit off at WA-Hwy 18 at Exit # 25 .
#Text=Go south on WA Hwy 18 through Tiger Mountain , Convington , Maple Valley and Auburn to Federal Way where WA-18 merges into I-5 .
#Text=Follow signs to I-5 south to Tacoma .
#Text=From Kitsap Peninsula Go south on Hwy 3 and follow signs for " WA-16 EAST to Port Orchard - Tacoma " .
#Text=Continue south along WA-16 through Gig Harbor and across the Tacoma Narrows Bridge into Tacoma .
#Text=There 's a toll to cross the Narrows Bridge into Tacoma but no toll coming the other way into Gig Harbor .
#Text=There are 5 exits into town from along WA-16 between the bridge and where the highway ends at I-5 .
#Text=Follows signs for I-5 " To Seattle " and exit at the next exit to I-705 to get downtown otherwise follow signs for I-5 south " To Portland " to get to the south or east part of town .
#Text=By bus

#Text=The bus station for Greyhound , Northwestern Trailways , Sound Transit , Intercity Transit , Pierce Transit & Link Light Rail is at the Tacoma Dome Station Parking Garage Buildings at 510 - 610 E Puyallup Ave ( facing E Puyallup Ave ) , between East E St and East G St , one block north of Freighthouse Square ( 2501 East D St ) .
#Text=Greyhound , NW Trailways and a taxi stand are at the west building while Sound Transit , Intercity & Pierce Transit buses are next door in front of the east building .
#Text=The Link Light Rail to downtown Tacoma is at the opposite side of the parking buildings along E 25th , between the E Parking Garage Building and the Freighthouse Square building :
#Text=Greyhound , Tacoma Dome Station , W Parking Bldg @ 510 E Puyallup Ave , ☏ +1253 383-4621 , toll-free : +1-800-231-2222 .

#Text=Travels primarily on Interstate 5 ( Seattle , Tacoma , Olympia , Centralia , Kelso/Longview and Portland . ) Passengers transfer in Seattle , Olympia or Portland to get to additional destinations .
#Text=Northwestern Trailways , Tacoma
#Text=Dome Station , W Parking Bldg 510 E Puyallup Ave , ☏ +1509 838-4029 , ✉ team@northwesterntrailways.com .
#Text=Goes north to Seattle and Everett along I-5 and then east to Lake Stevens , Leavenworth , Wenatchee , Ephrata , Moses Lake Ritzville & Spokane along US Hwy 2 and I-90 .
#Text=In Tacoma they stop at both the Greyhound station and the Amtrak station down the road .
#Text=Sound Transit , Tacoma
#Text=Dome Station , E Parking Bldg @ 610 E Puyallup Ave , ☏ +1-888-889-6368 .
#Text=Operates express routes between Lakewood , Tacoma & Seattle .
#Text=Rt #574 Seattle-Tacoma International Airport , Kent-Des Moines Hwy ( SR-516 ) , S 272nd St , Federal Way , Tacoma Dome & Lakewood
#Text=Rt#586 Downtown Tacoma//UW Tacoma , Tacoma Dome , University of Washington/U-District .
#Text=Northbound only during morning rush hours and southbound only during afternoon rush hours .
#Text=No stops in downtown Seattle
#Text=Rt#590,594 Downtown Seattle , Tacoma
#Text=Dome Station , Downtown Tacoma/UW Tacoma & Lakewood .
#Text=Rt 590 travels only between Downtown Tacoma , Tacoma Dome & Downtown Seattle during weekday rush hours only .
#Text=Rt#592 Downtown Seattle , Lakewood Park & Ride , Lakewood Sounder , Dupont .
#Text=Northbound only during morning rush hours and southbound only during afternoon rush hours .
#Text=No stops in downtown Tacoma or Tacoma Dome .
#Text=Rt#595 Downtown Seattle , Tacoma Community College ( TCC ) , Gig Harbor , Purdy .
#Text=Northbound only during morning rush hours and southbound only during afternoon rush hours .
#Text=No stops in downtown Tacoma or Tacoma Dome .
#Text=Link Light Rail runs frequent trains from Freighthouse Square to downtown Tacoma ( just north of 9th & Commerce ) .
#Text=The train goes by UW Tacoma , several museums , several downtown hotels and the downtown convention center .
#Text=The stop is along E 25th between the parking garage buildings and the Freighthouse Square building .
#Text=King County Metro , ☏ +1206 553-3000 .
#Text=Operates buses in and around Seattle and the surrounding cities and suburbs in King County .
#Text=Nearest transfer points to King County Metro from Tacoma are in Auburn , Federal Way/NE Tacoma and the Tahlequah ferry terminal ( Rt #118 , 119 ) in the south end of Vashon Island .
#Text=Intercity Transit , Tacoma
#Text=Dome Station , E Parking Bldg @ 610 E Puyallup Ave , ☏ +1360 786-1881 , toll-free : +1-800-287-6348 .
#Text=Operates express buses from downtown Tacoma and the Tacoma Dome Station down to Lacey ( Rt #612 ) and Olympia ( Rt #612 ) via Lakewood Station and Lakewood P&R during the work week only .
#Text=The #620 bus operates from the Tacoma Mall down to Olympia via Lakewood and Lacey on weekends only with no service to downtown Tacoma or Tacoma Dome Station .
#Text=They operate local buses in Lacey , Olympia and Tumwater .
#Text=Pierce Transit , ☏ +1253 581-8000 , toll-free : +1-800-562-8109 .
#Text=Operates local routes on buses that run on natural gas and connect with other regional transit systems .
#Text=Pierce transit can also be tracked with a free smartphone app from One Bus Away that provides easy access to real-time transit information for the Puget Sound region and beyond .

#Text=From the Tacoma Dome Station they go out to the surrounding cities and towns of Federal Way ( #500,501,574 ) ; Fife ( #500 ) ; Lakewood ( #574 , 594 or #3 from downtown ) ; Point Defiance Pk & the Ferry Terminal ( #11 , The #41 bus going from Tacoma Dome Station to downtown becomes the #11 ) ; Puyallup ( #400 ) ; Gig Harbor ( #102 during weekday rush hour or the #1 or #2 from downtown to TCC Transit Center & transfer to Rt #101 ) ; downtown Tacoma & UW Tacoma ( 13 , 14 , 41 , 500 , 501 , 586 , 594 & Link Light Rail ) Adult $ 2 , youth $ 0.75 and is part of the regional Orca payment system .
